The Chronicle Prosper Ndlovu, Business Editor BULAWAYO-based tannery, Boustead Leather, formerly Wet Blue Industries, says it is focused on regaining lost ground under a reviewed model that is anchored towards tapping into opportunities in the wider leather value chain. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-553278" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.24-2.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.24-2.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.24-2-360x200.jpeg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The company has acquired additional equipment and spare parts to upgrade its ageing plant, which has given the factory a new lease of life, Boustead Leather managing director, Mr Sibusiso Sibanda, said in an interview. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-553279" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.24.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.24.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.24-360x200.jpeg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “This is our 18th month since we took over operations as Boustead Leather and we are in a progressive position. There is enthusiasm from the team,” said Mr Sibanda. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-553282" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.25.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.25.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/WhatsApp-Image-2021-06-21-at-14.38.25-360x200.jpeg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “When we came here, this place was dead literally and we dedicated ourselves to reviving it. We started by reconnecting power supplies, fixing the water and sewer system and sprucing up the premises.” More to follow…